DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;
$a=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);
$b=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);
$c=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);

BEGIN_TEXT

$PAR
Let \(L\) be the length of the curve \(y=f(x),\,\,a \le x \le b,\) where \(f\) is positive and has a continuous derivative.  Let \(S\) be the surface area generated by rotating the curve about the \(x\)-axis.  If \(c\) is a positive constant, define \(g(x)=f(x)+c\) and let \(T\) be the corresponding surface area generated by the curve \(y=g(x),\,\,a \le x \le b.\)  Express \(T\) in terms of \(S\) and \(L\).

$PAR
\(T =\) \{ans_rule(30)\}

END_TEXT

ANS(fun_cmp("S+2*pi*c*L", var=>["S","c","L"], limits=>[[1,10],[1,10],[1,10]]));

ENDDOCUMENT();
